The invention will be better understood from studying the detailed description of a few embodiments taken by way of entirely nonlimiting examples and illustrated by the appended drawings, in which:


FIG. 1 is a view in axial section of a rolling bearing according to a first embodiment of the invention;


FIG. 2 is a half view in axial section of a rolling bearing according to a second embodiment of the invention;


FIG. 3 is a view similar to FIG. 2 showing a rolling bearing according to a third embodiment of the invention;


FIG. 4 is a view similar to FIG. 2 showing a rolling bearing according to a fourth embodiment of the invention;


FIG. 5 is a view similar to FIG. 2 showing a rolling bearing according to a fifth embodiment of the invention;.


FIG. 6 is a view similar to FIG. 2 showing a rolling bearing according to a sixth embodiment of the invention; and


FIG. 7 is a view similar to FIG. 1 showing the mounting of a rolling bearing in its final position;


FIG. 8 is a view in axial section of one embodiment of a rolling bearing with a built-in elastic washer;


FIG. 9 is a view in axial section of the rolling bearing according to FIG. 8 in the mounted position, with the elastic washer completely compressed;


FIG. 10 is a view in axial section of one embodiment of a rolling bearing comprising a locking washer with tabs that have axial elasticity;


FIG. 11 is a view in section of the rolling bearing according to FIG. 10 in the mounted position, with the elastic tabs of the locking washer fully flexed;


FIG. 12 is an axial view of the locking washer used in the rolling bearing of FIGS. 10 and 11; and


FIGS. 13 and 14 are partial sections on a larger scale on XIII--XIII and XIV--XIV of FIG. 12.
